filing algorithm is developed to generate HRR profiles without ghost images by using the least-squares (LS) estimation. For targets with negligible radial velocities, the new LS profiling algorithm can eliminate the ghost images successfully, and introduces less signal-to-noise ratio loss. With this algorithm, the restriction on the frequency step size is less rigid than the traditional unambiguous criterion. Consequently, a higher range resolution could be obtained. Simulations and field experimental results are also presented.", "references": [], "authors": [{"country": null, "city": null, "name": "Y. Liu", "affiliation": "Tsinghua University", "university": null}, {"country": null, "city": null, "name": "H. Meng", "affiliation": "Tsinghua University", "university": null}, {"country": null, "city": null, "name": "H. Zhang", "affiliation": "Tsinghua University", "university": null}, {"country": null, "city": null, "name": "X. Wang", "affiliation": "Tsinghua University", "university": null}], "publisher": "IET", "citations": [], "Metrics": {"Downloads (6 weeks) ": null, "Downloads (cumulative)": null, "Downloads (12 months)": null, "Citation Count": null}, "title": "Eliminating ghost images in high-range resolution profiles for stepped-frequency train of linear frequency modulation pulses", "arnumber": "5260398"}, "Article 2": {"doi": "10.1049/iet-rsn.2008.0082", "keywords": [{"type": "INSPEC: Controlled Indexing", "kwd": ["synthetic aperture radar", "Doppler radar", "radar detection", "radar imaging"]}, {"type": "INSPEC: Non-Controlled Indexing", "kwd": ["range instantaneous Doppler", "ISAR imaging", "inverse synthetic aperture radar imaging method", "manoeuvring targets", "range instantaneous chirp rate technique"]}], "abstract": "The conventional range instantaneous Doppler (RID) algorithm is a well accepted inverse synthetic aperture radar (ISAR) imaging method for manoeuvring targets. In the RID imaging, the cross-range resolution depends on the instantaneous Doppler of scatterers at the imaging instant. For a high manoeuvring target, the instantaneous Doppler of scatterers may be small at some imaging instants and the satisfactory RID images may not be obtained. On the other hand, a large instantaneous chirp rate is often present for the same scatterer at the same instant for RID imaging. In order to obtain some additional information of a manoeuvring target, a novel ISAR imaging approach, referred to as the range instantaneous chirp (RIC), is proposed based on instantaneous chirp rate of scatterer to provide cross-range resolution. Using the proposed imaging algorithm, with the same received data of RID, a RIC image is generated at the same instant with a different `view`. Therefore the RIC image may provide some additional information that is not shown in the RID image. With both the RIC and RID images, a better target recognition and identification can be achieved for high-manoeuvring targets. The proposed RIC algorithm is verified by raw radar data.", "references": [], "authors": [{"country": null, "city": null, "name": "G. Zhao-Zhao", "affiliation": "Xidian University", "university": null}, {"country": null, "city": null, "name": "L. Ya-Chao", "affiliation": "Xidian University", "university": null}, {"country": null, "city": null, "name": "X. Meng-Dao", "affiliation": "Xidian University", "university": null}, {"country": null, "city": null, "name": "W. Genyuan", "affiliation": "Xidian University", "university": null}, {"country": null, "city": null, "name": "Z. Shou-Hong", "affiliation": "Xidian University", "university": null}, {"country": null, "city": null, "name": "B. Zheng", "affiliation": "Xidian University", "university": null}], "publisher": "IET", "citations": [], "Metrics": {"Downloads (6 weeks) ": null, "Downloads (cumulative)": null, "Downloads (12 months)": null, "Citation Count": null}, "title": "ISAR imaging of manoeuvring targets with the range instantaneous chirp rate technique", "arnumber": "526039