Then, the corresponding electric fields received from the swell-contaminated sea surface are obtained. A Fourier transform of the autocorrelation of the electric fields gives the Doppler power spectral density (PSD), and a comparison between this PSD and monostatic radar range equation yields the radar cross-sections. Simulation shows that the assumption incorporating the coupling effects leads to results that better agree with historical field observations. Overall, the model proposed here not only lays a solid foundation for the development of future swell inversion algorithms, but also reveals the existence of non-linear energy transfer between swell and wind waves from a new perspective", "references": [], "authors": [{"country": null, "city": null, "name": "Chengxi Shen", "affiliation": "Faculty of Engineering and Applied Science, Memorial University of Newfoundland St. John's, New Foundland, Canada A1B 3X5", "university": null}, {"country": null, "city": null, "name": "Eric Gill", "affiliation": "Faculty of Engineering and Applied Science, Memorial University of Newfoundland St. John's, New Foundland, Canada A1B 3X5", "university": null}, {"country": null, "city": null, "name": "Weimin Huang", "affiliation": "Faculty of Engineering and Applied Science, Memorial University of Newfoundland St. John's, New Foundland, Canada A1B 3X5", "university": null}], "publisher": "IET", "citations": [], "Metrics": {"Downloads (6 weeks) ": null, "Downloads (cumulative)": null, "Downloads (12 months)": null, "Citation Count": null}, "title": "High-frequency radar cross-sections of swellcontaminated seas for a pulsed waveform", "arnumber": "6825712"}, "Article 2": {"doi": "10.1049/iet-rsn.2013.0108", "keywords": null, "abstract": "Time variation of micro-Doppler (mD) frequency is an important representation of target's micro-motions and intrinsic attributes in radar signals. For free rigid targets consisting of multiple scatterers, mixed mD time-frequency (TF) data sequences ba